    thinking: "**Structuring the Project**\n\nI\'m now focusing on setting up a robust folder structure. I\'ve decided on `/src/types/index.ts` to define data structures, including the profile mode config. The profile details will be stored in `/src/data/profileModes.ts` as a JSON configuration. Individual components will reside in `/src/components/`, ensuring modularity and maintainability.\n\n\n**Organizing File Structure**\n\nI\'m now expanding the file organization. I\'ve added `/src/sections/`, `/src/hooks/`, and `/src/services/` directories. My primary focus is `src/index.css`. I\'m integrating the specified premium fonts and custom theme utilities to reflect the desired typography. Tailwind v4 is used; now I\'ll use `@theme` to configure custom fonts, including \"Inter\" and another display font, per the guidelines\' focus on bold headings.\n\n\n"
    modified_response: "I will create `/src/types/index.ts` to model our dynamic, data-driven multi-role system. It will define types for Hero sections, projects, skills, history/journey, certifications, and blog recommendations to make the frontend easily pluggable to a FastAPI, Django, or Flask Python backend later."
