  planner_response {
    thinking: "**Confirming Initial Success**\n\nI\'m thrilled! The build ran flawlessly, no errors to report. Now, I\'m shifting focus to the user\'s request. My priority is confirming all design parameters are correctly understood and addressed, focusing on the frontend of an elite premium portfolio website for an ad.\n\n\n**Defining Aesthetic Direction**\n\nI\'ve got the foundational architecture locked down \342\200\223 clean, modular, and ready for a Python backend. It\'s set up with API abstraction and mock data. The visual style is taking shape: a blend of Apple\'s elegance with a luxury tech vibe, aiming for a distinctive, polished, and premium feel. Dark mode is an obsidian-luxury experience, light mode is a titanium-luxury experience. I\'ve integrated theme toggling and defined the typography scheme. The portfolio identity details are now clearly defined too.\n\n\n"
    modified_response: "I have designed and implemented the **elite, high-luxury premium portfolio website frontend** for **Adarsh Singh**. \n\nThe implementation acts as a beautiful fusion of **Apple Keynote**, **Luxury Automotive Tech**, and **Futuristic Minimalism**, perfectly conveying elite expertise while preserving recruiter readability.\n\n---\n\n### Key Visual & Architectural Highlights\n\n#### 1. **Multi-Role Content Morph Engine (Signature Feature)**\n- **Dynamic Configuration Layer (`/src/data/profileModes.ts` & `/src/types/index.ts`)**: Built a fully schema-validated data directory.\n- **Instant Metamorphosis**: Seamlessly switch between **General AI/Data** and **Data Engineer** modes via the sliding toggle in the floating navigation header. \n- **Adaptive Prioritization**: Toggle modes to reorder projects, sort primary technical categories, and adjust editorial recommendations on-the-fly without an abrupt page reload.\n  - *Generative AI & RAG* takes absolute priority in General mode.\n  - *Medallion ETL Pipelines, Databricks, and Apache Spark* snap to the top in Data Engineer mode.\n\n#### 2. **Titanium Light \342\206\224 Obsidian Dark Theme System**\n- **Obsidian Dark Theme**: Crafted around a deep matte background (`#050505`), utilizing graphite sheets, and a subtle electric blue/indigo ambient glow.\n- **Titanium Light Theme**: Employs clean silver gradients, soft diffused shadows, and premium white keynotes mirroring Apple\'s showcase layout.\n- **Advanced State Detection**: Combines system auto-preference matching (`prefers-color-scheme`) with persistent local storage caching.\n\n#### 3. **The Scenic Masterpiece: Floating Abstract Orb (Step 1)**\n- Renders a metallic and liquid liquid-mirror orb center on the right side of the hero section.\n- Orchestrates multi-layered surrounding glass orbital rings using CSS animations. The composition leverages gentle floating and breathing animation scales, delivering high-end technical depth.\n\n#### 4. **Asymmetrical Bento & Editorial Layouts (Steps 2, 3, & 4)**\n- **Interactive Bento Sheets**: Custom-crafted bento blocks featuring Adarsh\'s industry placement at **Capgemini** alongside verified certifications.\n- **The Accreditations Wall**: Eliminates generic, filler percentage meters in favor of verified credential indicators (AI-102, AWS Practitioner, Google Cloud GenAI, and AZ-204/900).\n- **Cinematic horizontal storytelling**: An interactive horizontal timeline tracking academic milestones, post-grad MCA specializations, and professional builder eras.\n- **Premium Newsletter Layout**: Displays editorial previews highlighting Adarsh\'s expertise in RAG structures and distributed infrastructure.\n\n#### 5. **Interactive Client Gateway & Abstraction Layer (Step 5)**\n- **Backend-Ready Abstraction (`/src/services/api.ts`)**: Pre-configured calls cleanly wrapped to decouple the UI from data fetching. The code is ready for seamless integration with a Python backend (FastAPI, Django, or Flask) by updating the `useMock` state.\n- **Interactive Contact Portal**: Captures props, handles submission lifecycle transitions, and shows real-time delivery status alerts.\n"
    thinking_duration {
      seconds: 3
      nanos: 184573373
    }
